            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1351049675,
            "creation_date": 1351049675,
            "body": "<p>use JScape's secure FTP library from <a href=\"http://www.jscape.com/blog/bid/74033/Secure-File-Transfer-with-Java-SFTP-Library\" rel=\"nofollow\">this link<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 13042635,
            "question_id": 13042616
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/XGeZl.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 193690,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 435583,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/435583/naytzyrhc",
                "reputation": 2317,
                "display_name": "Naytzyrhc"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1351050478,
            "creation_date": 1351049885,
            "body": "<p>given you have access to both peers, you can use <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/javax/net/ssl/SSLServerSocketFactory.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">SSLServerSocketFactory<\/a>/<a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/javax/net/ssl/SSLSocket.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">SSLSocket<\/a> for the connection on both ends.<\/p>\n\n<p>Edit:<\/p>\n\n<p>some basic example on how to establish connection and read/write data: <a href=\"http://stilius.net/java/java_ssl.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://stilius.net/java/java_ssl.php<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>wow, hope you are satisfied with our software :)<\/p>\n\n<p>thank you, <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 13042660,
